g.text: THE VARINT SQUEEZE: VARIABLE-LENGTH INTEGER SERIALIZATION

ol.li:
MSB (Bit 7):
1: This is NOT the last byte.
0: This IS the last byte.

Payload (Bits 0-6):
Pure data bits shifted into the final integer.

Storage:
Small ints (0-127) stay in 1 byte.
Large ints scale up to 9 bytes.

div.p: We divide the number into 7-bit groups. The 8th bit is reserved for the Continuation Flag.

g.title: Continuation Flag: 1 indicates the next byte is part of this number.
Termination Flag: 0 indicates the number ends here.
